'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Key Design Point |
    | 1 | Game orchestrates: board, dice, players, game loop | Orchestrator / Coordinator |
    | 2 | Board is 10x10 grid of Cells. Cell may have a Jump | Jump unifies Snake + Ladder |
    | 3 | Position (0-99) maps to Cell[row][col] | row = pos/size, col = pos%size |
    | 4 | Dice rolls 1-6 (configurable count) | Supports multiple dice |
    | 5 | Players rotate via deque (circular queue) | Round-robin, N-player support |
    | 6 | Loop: roll -> move -> jumpCheck -> update -> win check | Main game loop |
    | 7 | jumpCheck: start < end = ladder, start > end = snake | Unified jump model |
    |  |  |  |
    | **Core insight**: Snake and Ladder are the SAME class (Jump). No inheritance needed. | Direction determined by start vs end comparison. |  |
